The Grand Tree, or Ta Quir Priw in gnomish language, is home to a gnome community and is built inside a tree in the north-east of the Tree Gnome Stronghold. It contains Blurberry's Bar, Heckel Funch's Shop, Rometti's Fine Fashions, and Gulluck's weapon shop.

The Grand Tree includes two of the three banks in Tree Gnome Stronghold, several shops, and a bar and restaurant. The Gnome Restaurant minigame is on second level, and players who have completed The Grand Tree quest can access the Grand Tree Mine. There is an Agility shortcut north-east of the Grand Tree, which can be very useful for players training barbarian fishing.

Transportation[edit | edit source]

Players can travel to the Grand Tree via the gnome glider on the 3rd floor[UK]4th floor[US], or they can use seed pods from the Gnome Restaurant minigame to transport instantly to the Grand Tree. You may also use the royal seed pod after completion of Monkey Madness II. Just south of the tree itself is a Spirit Tree, and a landing spot for the Balloon Transport System. For those who don't have access to gnome glider or seed pods, you can also teleport to the Outpost using a necklace of passage and head north.

Ground floor[edit | edit source]

Players can find King Narnode Shareen on the ground floor[UK]1st floor[US]. Players can speak to him to begin (and later end) the Monkey Madness I quest. There is also a trapdoor that leads to the Grand Tree Tunnels (and a mine), though players must have completed The Grand Tree in order to use it.

First floor[edit | edit source]

The 1st floor[UK]2nd floor[US] includes two banks and several shops.

Third floor[edit | edit source]

The 3rd floor[UK]4th floor[US] contains only a small jail that Glough locks the player in during The Grand Tree quest, and a Gnome glider which can be used to travel to various places in Gielinor.

Tunnels and mine[edit | edit source]

Most of the tunnels are little used except during The Grand Tree quest. See Grand Tree Tunnels for details.

The mine contains adamantite, mithril, gold, coal, silver, iron, and clay rocks. See Grand Tree Mine for details.
